rComments: Honestly one of the best profs at Uottawa. The course is very content heavy but you are given a cool design project. YOU NEED HIS NOTES TO PASS THE COURSE.

Great prof and a nice guy. He genuinely knows the material and explains everything in great detail. His handwriting is somewhat difficult to read (sometimes unreadable) and he goes over a lot of material. However, the course was definitely worth taking.

He is a great prof! actually one of my favorite professors, but man his finals and midterms are very hard! He expects a lot out of his students which is why a lot of students dont like him. But if you're here to learn you will for sure learn a lot!

Overall, really a great prof ! Pros: Knows the subject, knows what he is talking about. This is the kind of prof where you will receive a great answer for any type of question.  Cons: Hand writing note hard to read, Don't know what to expect from his exams (all open book exams), Hardest final ever !

To counterbalance a prior rating.  This is a knowledgeable professor who expects students to work on the material.  If you want to learn something about numerical methods in EM, this is a great course.  I actually enjoyed the format of the assignments - learn by implementing the methods taught in class.
do not take any course with him

He knows his stuff well. The assignments are logical extension to what is discussed in the class. Tough final though. Overall I learned alot and worked for it, got a good grade. I wish more profs were like him.
prepare to get told you have no future
Nice guy, knows his material very well, although his midterm and final were a little tough, very fair guy
Nice guy, funny at times.  Midterms, Labs, and the Final were the hardest things ive ever attempted.  Scaling Mt. Everest with toothpick would be easier
